# Event Listeners ðŸ‘‚

The best way to handle events.

```javascript
const btn = document.querySelector('button');

btn.addEventListener('click', function() {
  alert("Button clicked!");
});
```

## Common Events
- `click`: Mouse click
- `mouseover` / `mouseout`: Hover
- `submit`: Form submission
- `keydown` / `keyup`: Keyboard input
- `load`: Page finished loading

# The Event Object ðŸ“¦

The event handler receives an `event` object with details.

```javascript
document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
  console.log(e.key); // Which key was pressed
});

form.addEventListener('submit', (e) => {
  e.preventDefault(); // STOP page refresh!
  console.log("Form submitted via JS");
});
```

# Event Flow ðŸŒŠ

## Bubbling
Events start at the target and bubble UP to parents.
Clicking a `<button>` inside a `<div>` triggers the button's click, then the div's click.

## Event Delegation
Instead of adding listeners to 100 list items, add ONE to the parent `<ul>`.

```javascript
list.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
  if (e.target.tagName === 'LI') {
    console.log("List item clicked");
  }
});
```
